\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang3081\b\fs28 CountDown\cf1\{keepn\}\cf0 
\par 
\par \b0\fs20 CountDown is a program which creates time-dependent sound files in MP3 format. 
\par 
\par If you need to create a sound file which plays an announcement at reguler pre-determined intervals, then you can use CountDown to generate the file you need. CountDown will not only build a file containing your recorded messages at the specified times, it can also include the time (or parts of it) into the message.
\par 
\par Once you have the sound file in MP3 format, you can play it on any MP3 compatible device, probably with some speakers hooked up to it.
\par 
\par \i Example
\par \i0 Suppose the organiser of an adventure race has teams departing at 5 minute intervals. For each group of starters there is a 30 second safety message to be delivered, then a check at 10 seconds to go and "GO !"  to start them. Once you have more than 4 or 5 groups of starter, its quite an effort to make sure that each start is told all of the information.
\par 
\par Using CountDown, the organiser could create a recording with the required information delivered right on time, with the relevant time included in the message.
\par 
\par }
