\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang3081\b\fs28 Schedule\cf1\{keepn\}\cf0 
\par \b0\fs20 The schedule is the list of all messages that are to be recorded. Each message is either a recorded message or a time message which will be generated by the program.
\par 
\par Each message can either have a start time independent of other messages, or it can follow on from an existing message.\lang1033\f1 
\par 
\par \lang3081\f0 Any schedule must specify the first time that an announcement is to be made for and the last time.
\par 
\par Messages can be deleted from the schedule by slecting them in the schedule list and then clicking the delete button.\lang1033\f1 
\par }
